State MSM Profile: Colorado

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Colorado

An estimated 73,357 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Colorado in 2013, representing 1.6% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 1,939,236 adult men of Colorado, 3.8% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Colorado resided in fringe counties of large metropolitan areas (41.3%). Including both central and fringe counties, 76.0% resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Colorado, 2013

MSM in Colorado Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Colorado, Denver County had the largest population of MSM at 25,464, representing 34.7% of all MSM in the state. Denver County also had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Colorado at 10.5%. This was greater than the percentage for Colorado as a whole, which was 3.8% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Colorado Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Denver-Aurora-Lakewood Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Denver-Aurora-Lakewood MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Colorado at 55,734, or 76.0% of all MSM in the state. Of the 967,728 adult men in Denver-Aurora-Lakewood, an estimated 5.8% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Colorado Springs Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Colorado Springs MSA had a population of 4,973 MSM, or 6.8% of all MSM in Colorado. Of the 242,960 adult men in Colorado Springs, an estimated 2.0% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Fort Collins Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Fort Collins MSA had a population of 2,441 MSM, or 3.3% of all MSM in Colorado. Of the 118,958 adult men in Fort Collins, an estimated 2.1% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Boulder Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Boulder MSA had a population of 2,274 MSM, or 3.1% of all MSM in Colorado. Of the 118,928 adult men in Boulder, an estimated 1.9% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Greeley Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Greeley MSA had a population of 1,441 MSM, or 2.0% of all MSM in Colorado. Of the 93,382 adult men in Greeley, an estimated 1.5% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Grand Junction Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Grand Junction MSA had a population of 1,208 MSM, or 1.6% of all MSM in Colorado. Of the 55,797 adult men in Grand Junction, an estimated 2.2% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Pueblo Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Pueblo MSA had a population of 1,037 MSM, or 1.4% of all MSM in Colorado. Of the 58,904 adult men in Pueblo, an estimated 1.8% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
